			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A cation-exchange resin is a cross-linked polymer with negatively charged structural units. It can exchange bound Na + (Kayexalate) or Ca 2+ (calcium resonium) for cations including K +. The purpose of using resins is to enhance the elimination of K + from the gastrointestinal tract. It is also a useful adjunct to the present treatment of congestive heart failure.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">阳离子交换树脂是一种带有负电荷结构单元的交联聚合物。它可以将结合的 Na +（萱草酸盐）或 Ca 2 +（钙共振）交换为包括 K + 在内的阳离子。使用树脂的目的是促进 K + 从胃肠道排出。它也是目前治疗充血性心力衰竭的有效辅助药物。</common:generalComment>
